          {
            "commit": "8c3e7e837e1f4cc5fc55df52e0dcd926af9a5e28",
            "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: add timeout to dynamic discovery thread"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-03-16 19:59:11.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-03-23 23:26:52.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: fix peer discovery shutdown",
        "message": "LU-9119 lnet: fix peer discovery shutdown\n\nThe code in lnet_peer_discovery() that handles shutdown of\ndiscovery doesn't properly free resources and uses\nlnet_for_each_entry() in an unsafe manner.\n\nWhen shutting down, do the following:\n\n1) Walk the working queue and call lnet_peer_discovery_timeout()\n   to stop any Ping or Push in progress on the peer. All peers\n   are moved to the expired queue.\n\n2) Wait for the event handler to run. This will move all peers\n   from the expired queue to the request queue.\n\n3) Clear the request queue by calling lnet_peer_discovery_error()\n   and lnet_peer_discovery_complete() on each peer. This removes\n   the peers from the request queue.\n\nAt this point the discovry queues are all empty and peer discovery\nshutdown is complete.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iacc443fbfcb55d086990994d3b7f6765e5526776\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
